# Naming Conventions

## Files

Use **kebab-case** for all file names:

```
✅ info-card.tsx
✅ quiz-data.ts
✅ generate-analysis.ts
✅ offer-page-content.tsx

❌ InfoCard.tsx
❌ quizData.ts
❌ generateAnalysis.ts
```

## Components

Use **PascalCase** for component names:

```typescript
✅ export function InfoCard() { ... }
✅ export function SingleChoiceStep() { ... }
✅ export default function QuizPage() { ... }

❌ export function infoCard() { ... }
❌ export function single_choice_step() { ... }
```

## Functions and Variables

Use **camelCase** for functions, variables, and hook names:

```typescript
✅ const stepProgress = 0.5;
✅ function setAnswer(key, value) { ... }
✅ const handleSelect = () => { ... };
✅ function useQuizKeyboard() { ... }

❌ const step_progress = 0.5;
❌ function SetAnswer() { ... }
```

## Constants

Use **UPPER_SNAKE_CASE** for constants:

```typescript
✅ const TOTAL_STEPS = 22;
✅ const DEFAULT_ANSWERS = { ... };
✅ const STORAGE_KEY = "carni-quiz";

❌ const totalSteps = 22;
❌ const defaultAnswers = { ... };
```

## Types and Interfaces

Use **PascalCase** for types and interfaces:

```typescript
✅ type Gender = "male" | "female";
✅ interface AnalysisResult { ... }
✅ type SingleChoiceProps = { ... };

❌ type gender = "male" | "female";
❌ interface analysisResult { ... }
```
